                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>\n                                        <date>26 Aug 1850</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My Dr Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I had sent my letter to the letters<lb/> Office\n                                        this morning when <persName>Mr Simmonds</persName> sent\n                                        me<lb/> a pack containing the Occident &amp;c &amp;c &amp;\n                                        your kind<lb/> favor of <date>July 3d</date> the vessel that\n                                        brought the parcel<lb/> arrived on the <date>22<hi\n                                                  rend=\"sup\">nd</hi></date> the pack for me must\n                                        have been<lb/> contained in his &amp; he was kind enough to\n                                        keep<lb/> mine 4 days, pitifully enough—therefore in\n                                        future<lb/> please send mine direct.</p>\n                              <p>I have read with much interest the review<lb/> &amp; was glad that\n                                        one honorable &amp; high minded man<lb/> was found to defend\n                                        you &amp; uphold the ministry,<lb/> his name should be\n                                        published, for honor is due<lb/> to him for the spirited\n                                        manner he shows up the<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> adjunto; now that the\n                                        affair &amp;<lb/> Resolution is printed I feel persuaded\n                                        that the<lb/> actors most regret the step taken. I am held\n                                        out<lb/> in this opinion by the election being\n                                        postponed<lb/> for such a length of time, it appears that\n                                        they<lb/> anticipate an arrangement with you. I council\n                                        you<lb/> by all means to be firm on the point, for I am<lb/>\n                                        persuaded that the more it is discussed the greater<lb/>\n                                        will be the increase of opinion in your favor, I have<lb/>\n                                        fought nearly the same battle here &amp; after much<lb/>\n                                        difficulty succeeded in placing the minister <del>in\n                                                  his</del></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3k931s45/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
